Shape Map 13

Further, in this step we are going to create US map in order to show number of infection by the virus through out the state.

Steps for this report

1. Drag and drop shape map from visualizations.

2. Drag and drop

  • state column from COVID-19 in US table to location in fields box
  •  Infection WOW% from  measures table to Color saturation in fields box
  • Infection rate from measure table to tooltips in fields box
  • Total cases from measure table to tooltips in fields box
  • Total infection from measure table to tooltips in fields box

3. format data colors,

  • Minimum - light gray
  • Maximum - dark orange

4. Shape- 

  • Map - USA(States)

5. Default color

  • Show - on
  • Color and Boarder color - Black 40 % lighter
  • Boarder thickness - 2

6. Zoom

  • Selection zoom - on

7. Add title and use same format through out the dashboard. (Refer step 4)

8. Boarder - on

  • Color - white 30% darker

9. Tooltips - on



How to create shape map?
(https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/power-bi/visuals/desktop-shape-map)
